{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πρόβᾰτον</b>, τό, <br /> frequently in <i>plural</i> πρόβατα (but also in <i>singular</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 43, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 302a, etc.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; irregular <i>dative</i> πρόβασι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Hdn.Gr. 1.414, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus:\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>] — used (among the Ionians and Dorians) of all four-footed <b>cattle,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.41, etc.; πάντων τῶν π. βόες μάλιστα ἀτονέουσι 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 8; τὰ ἄλλα π. καὶ ἵππους μάλιστα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.61, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 316, “IG” 12(1).677.31 (Rhodes, 4th-3rd c.BC) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Europa's bull, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 28: in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] generally of <b>cattle, flocks</b> and <b>herds,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.124, 23.550, “hymnus ad Mercurium” 571, compare “IG” 12(7).62.35 (Amorgos, 4th c.BC)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ π. καὶ καρταίποδα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Leg.Gort.” 4.35 \">Refs</a>]; opposed to ἄνθρωποι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 558, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.203 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ λεπτὰ τῶν π. small <b>cattle,</b> i.e. sheep and goats, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 133, 8.137; τὸ μὲν μέζον π..., τὸ δὲ μεῖον “IG” 5 (2).3.14 (Tegea, 4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; so later, π. ἀπὸ τῶν ἀρνῶν καὶ τῶν ἐρίφων λήψεσθε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Exo.12.5: but in _Attic dialect_ Prose and Comedy texts (never in Trag.)\">LXX</a>] almost invariably of <b>sheep,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 714, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.14, “IG” 22.1672.289, etc.; ὥσπερ π. βῆ βῆ λέγων βαδίζει 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 43 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so in later <i>Boeotian dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.3171.39,44 (Orchom. _Boeotian dialect_)\">Refs</a>]: generally, <b>animals for slaughter,</b> whether for sacrifices, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.56 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; or for food, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.207; compare 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.29. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> proverbial of stupid, lazy people, ἀριθμός, πρόβατ᾽ ἄλλως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1203, compare “V.” 32: Comedy texts _comparative_, προβάτου προβάτερον\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>more sheepish</b> than <b>a sheep,</b> uncertain conjecture in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 122 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρυσοῦν π., = Latin <i>pecus aurea,</i> as nickname, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 59.8 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: in other proverbs, τοὺς γευομένους κύνας τῶν π. κατακόπτειν φασὶ δεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.40; λέων ἐν προβάτοις 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Cleomenes” 33, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.35.13. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> name of a sea-fish, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 1.146, 3.139, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 9.38 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. (Orig. of small cattle, sheep and goats, which in primitive mixed herds <b>walk in front</b> (προβαίνει) of the larger animals.)","strongNumber":"G4263","accentedUnicode":"πρόβατον","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4262","matchingForm":"προβατικός","stepTransliteration":"probatikos","gloss":"Sheep Gate","_searchResultRange":"John.5.2@Neh.3.1-John.5.2","_zh_tw_Gloss":"羊門","_es_Gloss":"puerta de las Ovejas","_zh_Gloss":"羊门"}],"shortDef":"lamb","mediumDef":"a sheep, lamb","stepGloss":"sheep","stepTransliteration":"probaton","count":40,"_es_Definition":"oveja","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 羊<br>2) (神的子民) 羊","_zh_Definition":"1) 羊<br>2) (神的子民) 羊","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"con chiên; con cừu cái.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"羊","_es_Gloss":"oveja","_zh_Gloss":"羊"}]}